author: James Carmody
title: WA may be starting to 'flatten the curve', but that may lead to a range of new problems
description: The stream of COVID-19 cases in WA has slowed to a trickle in recent days, but this could mean WA would have to face tighter interstate travel restrictions for months after the rest of Australia has developed herd immunity.
content:
Updated 
April 01, 2020 08:33:38
The stream of COVID-19 cases in WA has slowed to a trickle in recent days, but WA Health Minister Roger Cook has made it clear the fight is not over it is just beginning.
